         <abstract>
            <p>We prove the nonlinear stability and convergence of a fully discrete, pseudospectral scheme for the "good" Boussinesq equation u&lt;sub&gt;tt&lt;/sub&gt; = -u&lt;sub&gt;xxxx&lt;/sub&gt; + u&lt;sub&gt;xx&lt;/sub&gt; + (u&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;)&lt;sub&gt;xx&lt;/sub&gt;. Numerical comparisons with finite difference schemes are also reported.</p>
          </abstract>
